\hich\af1\dbch\af16\loch\f1 Model for DMAware Open-Source Develo\hich\af1\dbch\af16\loch\f1 pment and Distribution
\par }\pard\plain \s17\li720\sb200\widctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {\cs25\i DMAware is the working name for the open-source development and distribution of document-management software based on the work of the AIIM Document Management Alliance.\~ }{

\par }\pard\plain \s18\li720\sb200\widctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {\cs25\i The subject matter of the DMAware clearinghouse is public, openly-contributed DMA software, documentation, and metadata definitions.\~ }{
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb200\widctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {\cs25\i The DMAware clearinghouse accepts other open-source contributions that further the integrated usage of standards-based document-management technology. \~\~
 Links are provided to other work that contributes to interoperability of document-management solutions.}{
\par }{\cs25\i This is a draft of in-progress work.\~ For access to the latest version, visit }{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst {\cs25\i  HYPERLINK "http://www.infonuovo.com/DMAware" }{\i {\*\datafield 
