}{\fldrslt {\cs26\ul\cf2 Change History}}}{" section added.\line references "}{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "" \\l "Top" }{{\*\datafield 08d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b02000000080000000400000054006f0070000000}}}{\fldrslt {\cs26\ul\cf2 
to Top of Document}}}{" corrected to be internal shortcuts and not web site references.\line Section }{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "" \\l "DerivedWorksAllowed" }{{\*\datafield 
08d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b020000000800000014000000440065007200690076006500640057006f0072006b00730041006c006c006f007700650064000000}}}{\fldrslt {\cs26\ul\cf2 3.2 (3)}}}{ updated to include requirement for deposit of derivative works and section }
{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "" \\l "SourceCodeInclusion" }{{\*\datafield 08d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b02000000080000001400000053006f00750072006300650043006f006400650049006e0063006c007500730069006f006e000000}}}{\fldrslt {\cs26\ul\cf2 
3.2 (2)}}}{ revised to allow access to source code to be satisfied by reference to the deposited copy.\line Remembered to run the FrontPage 98 spelling checker.\line "}{\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "" \\l "Contributors" }{{\*\datafield 
08d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b02000000080000000d00000043006f006e007400720069006200750074006f00720073000000}}}{\fldrslt {\cs26\ul\cf2 Contributors}}}{" section added.\line Changed titles in the References sections to also be hyperlinks to t
he sources, even though these may not be presented correctly on conversion to versions of Microsoft Word older than Word 97.\~ The references were revised to provide hyperlinks for all web-published materials and sources.\line 
Removed dates from section 9 and replaced section with a simple road map.\~ Clarified the separation between DMA 1.0 material and subsequent open-source materials.\line 
Copyright retention by AIIM is relaxed for material which is contributed under existing copyright, so long as the material is OSI-certified.\line Added more examples and cases for libraries and components in section 3.\line 
Affirmed that project management is intended to be light-weight, applies beyond initial contribution, and is more like having bylaws for a club\line Left open determination of
 whether or not derivative works must be redistributed under the same conditions (section 3.2 (3)).\line Provided more motivation for the purpose of library and component licenses separate from a general software license.\line 
Emphasized the special status of the DMA System Manager and the importance of having all applications and components installed on a computer be able to rely on a single, shared system-manager copy.\line Completed sections 1 and 2.\line 
Minor adjustments between the Word and HTML versions.
\par }\pard \ri720\sb200\widctlpar\adjustright {\cs27\b draft 0.01}{ 1999-11-10-12:00 pst (-0800) by dh
